#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2096
#, no-c-format
msgid "Custom Highlighting Text Styles"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2098
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here you can establish text styles for a specific syntax highlighting "
"definition, overriding the <userinput>default text style</userinput> "
"described in <link linkend=\"color-themes-text-styles\">the previous "
"section</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2103
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <link linkend=\"color-themes-json\">&JSON; theme file</link>, this "
"corresponds to the <userinput>custom-styles</userinput> key, whose value is "
"an <emphasis>object</emphasis> where each subschema key corresponds to the "
"<userinput>name of a syntax highlighting definition</userinput>. Its value "
"is an <emphasis>object</emphasis> where each key refers to the "
"<userinput>style attributes name</userinput> defined in <link linkend=\"kate-"
"highlight-sections\">the <userinput>itemData</userinput> elements</link> of "
"the syntax highlighting &XML; file, and the respective value is a sub-object "
"with the keys <emphasis>text-color</emphasis>, <emphasis>selected-text-"
"color</emphasis>, <emphasis>bold</emphasis>, <emphasis>italic</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>underline</emphasis>, <emphasis>strike-through</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>background-color</emphasis> and <emphasis>selected-background-"
"color</emphasis>, defined in <link linkend=\"color-themes-text-styles\">the "
"previous section</link>. Each of these values are optional, since if they "
"are not present, the style set in <userinput>text-styles</userinput> is "
"considered."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2116
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, in this piece of code, the <quote>ISO C++</quote> syntax "
"highlighting definition has a special text style for the <quote>Type "
"Modifiers</quote> and <quote>Standard Classes</quote> attributes. In the "
"corresponding &XML; file <quote>isocpp.xml</quote>, the defined attribute "
"<quote>Standard Classes</quote> uses the default style <userinput>BuiltIn</"
"userinput> (or dsBuiltIn). In this attribute, only the value of "
"<userinput>text-color</userinput> is overwritten by the new color "
"<quote>#6431b3</quote>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: programlisting
#: development.docbook:2124
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\"custom-styles\": {\n"
"    \"ISO C++\": {\n"
"        \"Standard Classes\": {\n"
"            \"text-color\": \"#6431b3\"\n"
"        },\n"
"        \"Type Modifiers\": {\n"
"            \"bold\": true,\n"
"            \"selected-text-color\": \"#009183\",\n"
"            \"text-color\": \"#00b5cf\"\n"
"        }\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You should consider that these text styles are associated with the attribute "
"names defined in the syntax highlighting &XML; files. If an XML file is "
"updated and some attributes are renamed or removed, the custom style defined "
"in the theme will no longer apply."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2136
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Syntax highlighting definitions often include other definitions. For "
"example, the <quote>QML</quote> highlighter includes the <quote>JavaScript</"
"quote> highlighter, since they share functionality in highlighting."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In <link linkend=\"color-themes-gui\">the &GUI; to manage themes of "
"KTextEditor</link>, these attributes can be modified in the "
"<userinput><guilabel>Highlighting Text Styles</guilabel></userinput> tab. By "
"default, the editor preselects the highlighting of the current document. You "
"will notice that many highlights contain other highlights represented by "
"groups in the style list. For example most highlights import the "
"<quote>Alert</quote> highlight, and many source code formats import the "
"<quote>Doxygen</quote> highlight."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2159
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Color Themes &GUI;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2161
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The simplest way to create and edit color themes is through the &GUI; within "
"the <link linkend=\"config-dialog\"><quote>Configure</quote> dialog</link> "
"provided by <ulink url=\"https://api.kde.org/frameworks/ktexteditor/html/"
"\">KTextEditor</ulink>. To access it, select <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Configure <replaceable>Application</replaceable>...</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> from the menubar in your text editor. This brings "
"up the <guilabel>Configure</guilabel> dialog box, there select "
"<guilabel>Color Themes</guilabel> in the side panel."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: phrase
#: development.docbook:2172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<phrase>&kate;'s settings dialog box with the color theme management.</"
"phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<para>&kate;'s settings dialog box with the color theme management.</para>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2177
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this <link linkend=\"config-dialog\">dialog</link> you can configure all "
"the colors in any theme you have, as well as create/copy new themes, delete "
"them, export them to a <userinput>.theme</userinput> file with <link linkend="
"\"color-themes-json\">&JSON; format</link> or import them from external "
"<userinput>.theme</userinput> files. Each theme has settings for text colors "
"and styles."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2184
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The built-in themes cannot be modified by default. To do this, you need to "
"copy them and give them a new name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2187
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use a theme permanently in your text editor, you must select it in the "
"combobox labeled <guilabel>Default theme for <replaceable>Application</"
"replaceable></guilabel> at the bottom of the dialog and press "
"<guibutton>Apply</guibutton> or <guibutton>OK</guibutton>. By default, the "
"<userinput><guilabel>Automatic Selection</guilabel></userinput> option is "
"active, which chooses a more appropriate color theme according to the "
"<emphasis>&kde; &plasma; color scheme</emphasis> used in the text editing "
"application; it usually chooses between <quote>Breeze Light</quote> and "
"<quote>Breeze Dark</quote> if the scheme is light or dark, respectively."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2198
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can adjust the &kde; global color scheme in the <ulink url=\"help:/"
"kcontrol/colors/\"><quote>Colors</quote> module in &systemsettings;</ulink>. "
"You can also change it in some applications individually such as &kate; or "
"&kdevelop;, from the menu <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu><guisubmenu>Color Scheme</guisubmenu></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2208
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a new theme"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create a new theme, it is first necessary to copy an existing one. Select "
"an existing theme which you want to use as a base, such as <quote>Breeze "
"Light</quote> or <quote>Breeze Dark</quote>, and click <guibutton>Copy</"
"guibutton>. Then write a name for the new theme."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2215
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to modify a built-in or read-only theme, you must first copy it "
"under a different name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2221
#, no-c-format
msgid "Import or export &JSON; theme files"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2223
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can export a selected theme (including built-in ones) to a <link linkend="
"\"color-themes-json\">&JSON; file</link> with <userinput>.theme</userinput> "
"extension, with the <guibutton>Export</guibutton> button. This will open a "
"dialog to save the file. To add a color theme from an external <link linkend="
"\"color-themes-json\">&JSON; file</link>, just press the <guibutton>Import</"
"guibutton> button and select the <userinput>.theme</userinput> file from the "
"dialog."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2236
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As <link linkend=\"color-themes-json-overview\">mentioned above</link>, user-"
"customized theme files are stored in the <filename class=\"directory\">org."
"kde.syntax-highlighting/themes/</filename> directory. When you copy or "
"create a theme, it will automatically appear there. Also, importing or "
"adding a theme is equivalent to copying an external <userinput>.theme</"
"userinput> file into this directory. KSyntaxHighlighting automatically picks "
"up color theme files from this directory."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2244
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to publish a theme created by you, it is essential to check the "
"<link linkend=\"color-themes-json-metadata\">metadata</link> object of the "
"<link linkend=\"color-themes-json\">&JSON; file</link>, adding the "
"respective license and checking the revision number."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2257
#, no-c-format
msgid "Editing color themes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2261
#, no-c-format
msgid "Colors"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2263
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here the colors of the text editing area are adjusted. These are detailed in "
"<xref linkend=\"color-themes-editor-colors\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2276 development.docbook:2296
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The name in the list of styles is using the style configured for the item, "
"providing you with an immediate preview when configuring a style."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2279
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each style lets you select common attributes as well as foreground and "
"background colors. To unset a background color, right-click to use the "
"context menu."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2282
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The attributes of this area are detailed in <xref linkend=\"color-themes-"
"text-styles\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2289
#, no-c-format
msgid "Highlighting Text Styles"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2291
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here you can edit the text styles used by a specific highlight definition. "
"The editor preselects the highlight used by your current document. To work "
"on a different highlight, select one in the <guilabel>Highlight</guilabel> "
"combobox above the style list."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2299
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each style lets you select common attributes as well as foreground and "
"background colors. To unset a background color, right-click to use the "
"context menu. In addition you can see if a style is equal to the default "
"style used for the item, and set it to that if not."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2303
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You will notice that many highlights contain other highlights represented by "
"groups in the style list. For example most highlights import the Alert "
"highlight, and many source code formats imports the Doxygen highlight. "
"Editing colors in those groups only affects the styles when used in the "
"edited highlight format."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2322
#, no-c-format
msgid "Contrast of Text Colors"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2324
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An important aspect when working with color themes is to choose a text "
"contrast that makes it easier to read, especially in combination with the "
"background."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2327
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>Kontrast</userinput> application is a color contrast checker. "
"It tells you that the text color and background color combinations are "
"readable and accessible, so this is an excellent tool to help you create "
"color themes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2331
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can download <userinput>Kontrast</userinput> from <ulink url=\"https://"
"apps.kde.org/en/kontrast\">the &kde; Applications website</ulink> or from "
"<ulink url=\"https://flathub.org/apps/details/org.kde.kontrast\">the Flatpak "
"package on Flathub</ulink> (only in GNU/Linux)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2336
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The GNOME <userinput>Contrast</userinput> application is similar. You can "
"download <ulink url=\"https://flathub.org/apps/details/org.gnome.design."
"Contrast\">the Flatpak package on Flathub</ulink> (only in GNU/Linux)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A python script in <ulink url=\"https://invent.kde.org/frameworks/syntax-"
"highlighting/-/blob/master/utils/theme_contrast_checker.py?ref_type=heads"
"\">Syntax Highlighting repository</ulink> lets you visualize all the colors "
"in a theme, as well as the contrast with the various backgrounds configured."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2348
#, no-c-format
msgid "Suggestions of Consistency with Syntax Highlighting"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2350
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"KSyntaxHighlighting includes <ulink url=\"https://kate-editor.org/syntax/"
"\">more than 300 syntax highlighting definitions</ulink>, therefore it is "
"ideal that you make sure your new theme looks good in all syntax "
"highlighting definitions. The built-in color themes have the following "
"similarities that it is recommended (but not required) to follow to achieve "
"a correct display of all syntax highlighting definitions:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2358
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use bold for the <quote>Keyword</quote> and <quote>ControlFlow</quote> <link "
"linkend=\"color-themes-text-styles\">text styles</link>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2361
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Do not use background color in any <link linkend=\"color-themes-text-styles"
"\">text style</link>, except <quote>Alert</quote> and <quote>RegionMarker</"
"quote>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2366
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most of the syntax highlighters are intended to look good on the default "
"themes <quote>Breeze Light</quote> and <quote>Breeze Dark</quote>, "
"therefore, another way to maintain consistency is to use similar colors in "
"the <link linkend=\"color-themes-text-styles\">text styles</link>, like "
"<emphasis>green</emphasis> for <quote>Preprocessor</quote> and "
"<quote>Others</quote>, <emphasis>blue</emphasis> for <quote>DataType</quote> "
"and <quote>Attribute</quote>, or <emphasis>purple</emphasis> for "
"<quote>Function</quote>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2374
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that these recommendations are not mandatory when creating and "
"publishing a theme."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2385
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scripting with &javascript;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2387
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Since &kappname; 3.4 in KDE 4.4 the &kappname; editor component is easily "
#| "extensible by writing scripts. The scripting language is ECMAScript "
#| "(widely known as JavaScript). &kappname; supports two kinds of scripts: "
#| "indentation and command line scripts."
msgid ""
"The &kappname; editor component is easily extensible by writing scripts. The "
"scripting language is ECMAScript (widely known as &javascript;). &kappname; "
"supports two kinds of scripts: indentation and command line scripts. A "
"functionality similar to command line scripts is also provided in the <ulink "
"url=\"help:/kate/kate-application-plugin-snippets.html\">snippets plugin</"
"ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Desde a versión 3.4 de &kappname;, incluída na versión 4.4 da colección de "
"software de KDE, pode ampliarse a funcionalidade do compoñente de edición de "
"&kappname; mediante scripts. A linguaxe a empregar para estes scripts é "
"ECMAScript (máis coñecida como JavaScript). &kappname; permite dous tipos de "
"scripts: de sangrado e da liña de ordes."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2396
#, no-c-format
msgid "Indentation Scripts"
msgstr "Guións de sangrado"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2398
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Indentation scripts - also referred as indenters - automatically indent "
#| "the source code while typing text. As example, after hitting the return-"
#| "key code the indentation level often increases."
msgid ""
"Indentation scripts - also referred as indenters - automatically indent the "
"source code while typing text. As an example, after hitting the return key "
"the indentation level often increases."
msgstr ""
"Os scripts de sangrado axustan o sangrado do código fonte a medida que se "
"escribe. Por exemplo, despois de premer a tecla Intro adoita aumentarse o "
"nivel de sangrado."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2404
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The following sections describe step by step how to create the skeleton "
#| "for a simple indenter. As first step, create a new <filename>*.js</"
#| "filename> file called e.g. <filename>javascript.js</filename> in the "
#| "local home folder <filename>$KDEHOME/share/apps/katepart/script</"
#| "filename>."
msgid ""
"The following sections describe step by step how to create the skeleton for "
"a simple indenter. As a first step, create a new <filename>*.js</filename> "
"file called &eg; <filename>javascript.js</filename> in the local home folder "
"<filename>$<envar>XDG_DATA_HOME</envar>/katepart5/script/indentation</"
"filename>. Therein, the environment variable <envar>XDG_DATA_HOME</envar> "
"typically expands to either <filename>~/.local</filename> or <filename>~/."
"local/share</filename>."
msgstr ""
"As seguintes seccións describen paso a paso como crear o esqueleto dun "
"script de sangrado sinxelo. O primeiro paso consistirá en crear un ficheiro "
"<filename>*.js</filename> —por exemplo, <filename>javascript.js</filename>— "
"no cartafol <filename>$KDEHOME/share/apps/katepart/script</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2412 development.docbook:2502
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On &Windows; these files are located in <filename>%USERPROFILE%\\AppData"
"\\Local\\katepart5\\script\\indentation</filename>. <replaceable>%USERPROFILE"
"%</replaceable> usually expands to <filename>C:\\\\Users\\"
"\\<replaceable>user</replaceable></filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2416
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Indentation Script Header"
msgstr "Cabeceira"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2417
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The header of the file <filename>javascript.js</filename> is embedded in "
#| "a comment and is of the following form <programlisting>\n"
#| "/* kate-script\n"
#| " * name: JavaScript\n"
#| " * author: Example Name &lt;example.name@some.address.org&gt;\n"
#| " * license: BSD\n"
#| " * revision: 1\n"
#| " * kate-version: 3.4\n"
#| " * type: indentation\n"
#| " * required-syntax-style: javascript\n"
#| " * indent-languages: javascript\n"
#| " * priority: 0\n"
#| " * i18n-catalog: mycatalog\n"
#| " *\n"
#| " * A line without colon ':' stops header parsing. That is, you can add "
#| "optional\n"
#| " * text here such as a detailed license.\n"
#| " */\n"
#| "</programlisting> Each entry is explained in detail now:"
msgid ""
"The header of the file <filename>javascript.js</filename> is embedded as "
"&JSON; at the beginning of the document as follows: <programlisting>\n"
"var katescript = {\n"
"    \"name\": \"JavaScript\",\n"
"    \"author\": \"Example Name &lt;example.name@some.address.org&gt;\",\n"
"    \"license\": \"BSD License\",\n"
"    \"revision\": 1,\n"
"    \"kate-version\": \"5.1\",\n"
"    \"required-syntax-style\": \"javascript\",\n"
"    \"indent-languages\": [\"javascript\"],\n"
"    \"priority\": 0,\n"
"}; // kate-script-header, must be at the start of the file without comments\n"
"</programlisting> Each entry is explained in detail now:"
msgstr ""
"A cabeceira do ficheiro <filename>javascript.js</filename> escríbese nun "
"comentario e ten a seguinte forma: <programlisting>\n"
"/* kate-script\n"
" * name: JavaScript\n"
" * author: Rosalía de Castro &lt;rosaliadecastro@example.com&gt;\n"
" * license: BSD\n"
" * revision: 1\n"
" * kate-version: 3.4\n"
" * type: indentation\n"
" * required-syntax-style: javascript\n"
" * indent-languages: javascript\n"
" * priority: 0\n"
" * i18n-catalog: catálogo_persoal\n"
" *\n"
" * A partir da primeira liña sen dous puntos («:») remata a análise\n"
" * da cabeceira, polo que pode empregar o comentario para\n"
" * texto adicional, como por exemplo detalles sobre a licencia\n"
" * do script.\n"
" */\n"
"</programlisting> A continuación explícanse punto por punto todas as "
"entradas definidas na cabeceira:"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2424
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>name</literal> [required]: This is the indenter name that appears "
"in the menu <menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Indentation</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> and in the configuration dialog."
msgstr ""
"<literal>name</literal> (obrigatorio). Este é o nome do guión de sangrado, o "
"que aparecerá no menú <menuchoice><guimenu>Utilidades</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Sangrado</guimenuitem></menuchoice> e no diálogo de "
"configuración."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2429 development.docbook:2558
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>author</literal> [optional]: The author's name and contact "
"information."
msgstr ""
"<literal>author</literal> (opcional). O nome de autor e a información de "
"contacto."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2432
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<literal>license</literal> [optional]: Short form of the license, such as "
#| "BSD or LGPLv3."
msgid ""
"<literal>license</literal> [optional]: Short form of the license, such as "
"BSD License or LGPLv3."
msgstr ""
"<literal>license</literal> (opcional). Abreviatura da licenza. Por exemplo: "
"BSD ou LGPLv3."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2435 development.docbook:2560
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>revision</literal> [required]: The revision of the script. This "
"number should be increased whenever the script is modified."
msgstr ""
"<literal>revision</literal> (obrigatorio). O número de revisión do guión. "
"Este número debería aumentarse cada vez que se modifique o guión."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2438 development.docbook:2561
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<literal>kate-version</literal> [required]: Minimal required &kappname; "
#| "version."
msgid ""
"<literal>kate-version</literal> [required]: Minimum required &kappname; "
"version."
msgstr ""
"<literal>kate-version</literal> (obrigatorio). A versión mínima de "
"&kappname; necesaria para empregar o script."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2441
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<literal>required-syntax-style</literal> [optional]: Comma separated list "
#| "of required syntax highlighting styles. This is important for indenters "
#| "that rely on specific highlight information in the document. If a "
#| "required syntax style is specified, the indenter is available only when "
#| "the appropriate highlighter is active. This prevents <quote>undefined "
#| "behavior</quote> caused by using the indenter without the expected "
#| "highlighting schema. For instance, the Ruby indenter makes use of this in "
#| "the files <filename>ruby.js</filename> and <filename>ruby.xml</filename>."
msgid ""
"<literal>required-syntax-style</literal> [optional]: The required syntax "
"style, which matches the specified <literal>style</literal> in syntax "
"highlighting files. This is important for indenters that rely on specific "
"highlight information in the document. If a required syntax style is "
"specified, the indenter is available only when the appropriate highlighter "
"is active. This prevents <quote>undefined behavior</quote> caused by using "
"the indenter without the expected highlighting schema. For instance, the "
"Ruby indenter makes use of this in the files <filename>ruby.js</filename> "
"and <filename>ruby.xml</filename>."
msgstr ""
"<literal>required-syntax-style</literal> (opcional). Lista, separada por "
"comas, de estilos de realzado de sintaxe que o script necesita. Isto é "
"importante para aqueles scripts que dependen de información de realzado "
"específica no documento. De indicarse un estilo de sintaxe necesario, o "
"script de sangrado só estará dispoñíbel cando ese script de realzado estea "
"activo. Así se evitan <quote>comportamentos inesperados</quote>, causados "
"polo uso de scripts de sangrado sen o esquema de realzado do que estes "
"dependen. Por exemplo, o script de sangrado de Ruby emprega esta opción nos "
"ficheiros <filename>ruby.js</filename> e <filename>ruby.xml</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2444
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<literal>indent-languages</literal> [optional]: Comma separated list of "
#| "syntax styles the indenter can indent correctly, e.g.: c++, java."
msgid ""
"<literal>indent-languages</literal> [optional]: &JSON; array of syntax "
"styles the indenter can indent correctly, &eg;: <literal>[\"c++\", \"java"
"\"]</literal>."
msgstr ""
"<literal>indent-languages</literal> (opcional). Lista, separada por comas, "
"de estilos de realzado que o script pode sangrar correctamente. Por exemplo: "
"c++, java."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2447
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>priority</literal> [optional]: If several indenters are suited for "
"a certain highlighted file, the priority decides which indenter is chosen as "
"default indenter."
msgstr ""
"<literal>priority</literal> (opcional). Se existen varios guións de sangrado "
"axeitados para un ficheiro de realzado concreto, o valor desta opción, a "
"prioridade, determina cal dos guións de sangrado se escolle de maneira "
"predeterminada."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2456
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Indenter Source Code"
msgstr "Código"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2457
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Having specified the header this section explains how the indentation "
#| "scripting itself works. The basic skeleton of the body looks like this: "
#| "<programlisting>\n"
#| "triggerCharacters = \"{}/:;\";\n"
#| "function indent(line, indentWidth, ch)\n"
#| "{\n"
#| "    // called for each newline (ch == '\\n') and all characters specified "
#| "in\n"
#| "    // the global variable triggerCharacters. When calling "
#| "<menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Align</guimenuitem></"
#| "menuchoice>\n"
#| "    // the variable ch is empty, i.e. ch == ''.\n"
#| "    //\n"
#| "    // see also: Scripting API\n"
#| "    return -2;\n"
#| "}\n"
#| "</programlisting> The function <function>indent()</function> has three "
#| "parameters: <itemizedlist> <listitem><para><literal>line</literal>: the "
#| "line that has to be indented</para></listitem> "
#| "<listitem><para><literal>indentWidth</literal>: the indentation width in "
#| "amount of spaces</para></listitem> <listitem><para><literal>ch</literal>: "
#| "either a newline character (<literal>ch == '\\n'</literal>), the trigger "
#| "character specified in <literal>triggerCharacters</literal> or empty if "
#| "the user invoked the action <menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>Align</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.</para></listitem> "
#| "</itemizedlist> The return value of the <function>indent()</function> "
#| "function specifies how the line will be indented. If the return value is "
#| "a simple integer number, it is interpreted as follows: <itemizedlist> "
#| "<listitem><para>return value <literal>-2</literal>: do nothing</para></"
#| "listitem> <listitem><para>return value <literal>-1</literal>: keep "
#| "indentation (searches for previous non-blank line)</para></listitem> "
#| "<listitem><para>return value <literal> 0</literal>: numbers &gt;= 0 "
#| "specify the indentation depth in spaces</para></listitem> </itemizedlist> "
#| "Alternatively, an array of two elements can be returned: <itemizedlist> "
#| "<listitem><para><literal>return [ indent, align ];</literal></para></"
#| "listitem> </itemizedlist> In this case, the first element is the "
#| "indentation depth like above with the same meaning of the special values. "
#| "However, the second element is an absolute value representing a column "
#| "for <quote>alignment</quote>. If this value is higher than the indent "
#| "value, the difference represents a number of spaces to be added after the "
#| "indentation of the first parameter. Otherwise, the second number is "
#| "ignored. Using tabs and spaces for indentation is often referred to as "
#| "<quote>mixed mode</quote>."
msgid ""
"Having specified the header this section explains how the indentation "
"scripting itself works. The basic skeleton of the body looks like this: "
"<programlisting>\n"
"// required katepart js libraries, &eg; range.js if you use Range\n"
"require (\"range.js\");\n"
"\n"
"triggerCharacters = \"{}/:;\";\n"
"function indent(line, indentWidth, ch)\n"
"{\n"
"    // called for each newline (ch == '\\n') and all characters specified "
"in\n"
"    // the global variable triggerCharacters. When calling "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</guimenu><guimenuitem>Format Indentation</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>\n"
"    // the variable ch is empty, i.e. ch == ''.\n"
"    //\n"
"    // see also: Scripting API\n"
"    return -2;\n"
"}\n"
"</programlisting> The function <function>indent()</function> has three "
"parameters: <itemizedlist> <listitem><para><literal>line</literal>: the line "
"that has to be indented</para></listitem> "
"<listitem><para><literal>indentWidth</literal>: the indentation width in "
"number of spaces</para></listitem> <listitem><para><literal>ch</literal>: "
"either a newline character (<literal>ch == '\\n'</literal>), the trigger "
"character specified in <literal>triggerCharacters</literal> or empty if the "
"user invoked the action <menuchoice><guimenu>Tools</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Format Indentation</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.</para></"
"listitem> </itemizedlist> The return value of the <function>indent()</"
"function> function specifies how the line will be indented. If the return "
"value is a simple integer number, it is interpreted as follows: "
"<itemizedlist> <listitem><para>return value <literal>-2</literal>: do "
"nothing</para></listitem> <listitem><para>return value <literal>-1</"
"literal>: keep indentation (searches for previous non-blank line)</para></"
"listitem> <listitem><para>return value <literal> 0</literal>: numbers &gt;= "
"0 specify the indentation depth in spaces</para></listitem> </itemizedlist> "
"Alternatively, an array of two elements can be returned: <itemizedlist> "
"<listitem><para><literal>return [ indent, align ];</literal></para></"
"listitem> </itemizedlist> In this case, the first element is the indentation "
"depth as above with the same meaning of the special values. However, the "
"second element is an absolute value representing a column for "
"<quote>alignment</quote>. If this value is higher than the indent value, the "
"difference represents a number of spaces to be added after the indentation "
"of the first parameter. Otherwise, the second number is ignored. Using tabs "
"and spaces for indentation is often referred to as <quote>mixed mode</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Unha vez escrita a cabeceira, é hora de escribir o código que determina a "
"lóxica do script de sangrado. O esqueleto básico do corpo ten o seguinte "
"aspecto: <programlisting>\n"
"triggerCharacters = \"{}/:;\";\n"
"function indent(line, indentWidth, ch)\n"
"{\n"
"    // Esta función execútase para cada nova liña (ch == '\\n') e para\n"
"    // todos os caracteres indicados na variábel global triggerCharacters.\n"
"    // Cando se executa <menuchoice><guimenu>Utilidades</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Aliñar</guimenuitem></menuchoice>\n"
"    // o parámetro ch chega baleiro, é dicir, ch == ''.\n"
"    //     // Vexa tamén a información da sección «API para scripts», máis "
"abaixo.    return -2;\n"
"}\n"
"</programlisting>  A función <function>indent()</function> recibe tres "
"parámetros: <itemizedlist>   <listitem><para><literal>line</literal>. A liña "
"cuxo sangrado debe axustarse.</para></listitem>   "
"<listitem><para><literal>indentWidth</literal>. A anchura do sangrado, "
"medida en cantidade de espazos.</para></listitem>   "
"<listitem><para><literal>ch</literal>. Un carácter de salto de liña "
"(<literal>ch == '\\n'</literal>), o carácter disparador indicado en "
"<literal>triggerCharacters</literal> ou unha cadea baleira se o usuario "
"executou a acción <menuchoice><guimenu>Utilidades</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Aliñar</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.</para></listitem> </"
"itemizedlist>  O valor que devolva a función <function>indent()</function> "
"determinará o sangrado da liña. De tratarse dun número enteiro, "
"interpretarase da seguinte maneira: <itemizedlist>   "
"<listitem><para><literal>-2</literal>. Non facer nada.</para></listitem>   "
"<listitem><para><literal>-1</literal>. Manter o sangrado da primeira liña "
"non baleira anterior á actual.</para></listitem>   <listitem><para><literal> "
"0</literal>. Os números positivos, incluído o 0, indican o nivel de sangrado "
"a aplicar á liña, en espazos.</para></listitem> </itemizedlist> En vez dun "
"enteiro, é posíbel devolver unha matriz de dous elementos: <itemizedlist>   "
"<listitem><para><literal>[ sangrado, aliñación ];</literal></para></"
"listitem> </itemizedlist> Neste caso, o primeiro elemento correspóndese co "
"nivel de sangrado, igual que cando se devolve un número enteiro. Pola outra "
"banda, o segundo elemento é un valor absoluto que representa a columna para "
"a <quote>aliñación</quote>. Se o valor é superior ao valor de sangrado, a "
"diferencia representa un número de espazos a engadir tras o sangrado do "
"primeiro parámetro (o <quote>sangrado</quote>). En caso contrario, este "
"segundo número ignorarase. Ao uso de tabulacións e espazos para o sangrado "
"adoita chamárselle <quote>modo mixto</quote>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2489
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Consider the following example: Assume using tabs to indent, and tab width "
"is set to 4. Here, &lt;tab&gt; represents a tab and '.' a space: "
"<programlisting>\n"
"1: &lt;tab&gt;&lt;tab&gt;foobar(\"hello\",\n"
"2: &lt;tab&gt;&lt;tab&gt;.......\"world\");\n"
"</programlisting> When indenting line 2, the <function>indent()</function> "
"function returns [8, 15]. As result, two tabs are inserted to indent to "
"column 8, and 7 spaces are added to align the second parameter under the "
"first, so that it stays aligned if the file is viewed with a different tab "
"width."
msgstr ""
"Digamos, por exemplo, que estamos a usar tabulacións para o sangrado, e que "
"a anchura das tabulacións é 4. Aquí, &lt;tab&gt; representa unha tabulación "
"e «.» un espazo: <programlisting>\n"
"1: &lt;tab&gt;&lt;tab&gt;funcion(\"Ola,\",\n"
"2: &lt;tab&gt;&lt;tab&gt;....…\"mundo!\");\n"
"</programlisting> Ao estabelecerse o sangrado da liña 2, a función "
"<function>indent()</function> devolve [8, 15]. Como resultado, insírense "
"dúas tabulacións para levar o sangrado ata a columna 8, e 7 espazos para "
"aliñar o segundo parámetro baixo o primeiro, de xeito que ambos permanezan "
"aliñados independentemente da anchura que os distintos editores de textos "
"cos que se abra o ficheiro usen para as tabulacións."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2499
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "A default KDE installation ships &kappname; with several indenters. The "
#| "corresponding JavaScript source code can be found in <filename>$KDEDIR/"
#| "share/apps/katepart/script</filename>."
msgid ""
"A default &kde; installation ships &kappname; with several indenters. The "
"corresponding &javascript; source code can be found in <filename>"
"$<envar>XDG_DATA_DIRS</envar>/katepart5/script/indentation</filename>."
msgstr ""
"A instalación predeterminada da colección de software de KDE fornece varios "
"scripts de sangrado para &kappname;. O seu código fonte está dispoñíbel no "
"cartafol <filename>$KDEDIR/share/apps/katepart/script</filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2506
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Developing an indenter requires to reload the scripts to see whether the "
#| "changes behave appropriately. Instead of restarting the application, "
#| "simply switch to the command line and invoke the command <command>reload-"
#| "scripts</command>."
msgid ""
"Developing an indenter requires reloading the scripts to see whether the "
"changes behave appropriately. Instead of restarting the application, simply "
"switch to the command line and invoke the command <command>reload-scripts</"
"command>."
msgstr ""
"Ao desenvolver un script de sangrado, é necesario recargar os scripts para "
"comprobar se os cambios funcionan como se espera. En vez de reiniciar o "
"aplicativo, é posíbel recargalos empregando a orde <command>reload-scripts</"
"command> desde a liña de ordes."

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2512 development.docbook:2624
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If you develop useful scripts please consider contributing to the "
#| "&kappname; Project by <ulink url=\"mailto:kwrite-devel@kde.org"
#| "\">contacting the mailing list</ulink>."
msgid ""
"If you develop useful scripts please consider contributing to the &kappname; "
"Project by providing a merge request to <ulink url=\"https://invent.kde.org/"
"frameworks/ktexteditor\">our GitLab project</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Se desenvolve scripts útiles, considere a posibilidade de doalos ao Proxecto "
"&kappname;. Pode contactar connosco (en inglés) mediante a nosa <ulink url="
"\"mailto:kwrite-devel@kde.org\">lista de correo</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: development.docbook:2521
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command Line Scripts"
msgstr "Guións da liña de ordes"

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2524
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A functionality similar to command line scripts is also provided in the "
"<ulink url=\"help:/kate/kate-application-plugin-snippets.html\">snippets "
"plugin</ulink>. This plugin may provide an easier starting point, especially "
"for small custom scripts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:2529
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "As it is hard to satisfy everyone's needs, &kappname; supports little "
#| "helper tools for quick text manipulation through the <link linkend="
#| "\"advanced-editing-tools-commandline\">built-in command line</link>. For "
#| "instance, the command <command>sort</command> is implemented as script. "
#| "This section explains how to create <filename>*.js</filename> files to "
#| "extend &kappname; with arbitrary helper scripts."
msgid ""
"As it is hard to satisfy everyone's needs, &kappname; supports little helper "
"tools for quick text manipulation through the <link linkend=\"advanced-"
"editing-tools-commandline\">built-in command line</link>. For instance, the "
"command <command>sort</command> is implemented as a script. This section "
"explains how to create <filename>*.js</filename> files to extend &kappname; "
"with arbitrary helper scripts."
msgstr ""
"Dado o difícil que resulta compracer a todos, &kappname; permite a "
"definición de pequenas ferramentas de asistencia para a manipulación rápida "
"de texto mediante a <link linkend=\"advanced-editing-tools-commandline"
