#. Tag: para
#: development.docbook:3002
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The translation functions translate the wrapped strings through KDE's "
#| "translation system to the language used in the application. Strings in "
#| "scripts being developed in the official &kappname; sources are "
#| "automatically extracted and translatable. In other words, as a &kappname; "
#| "developer you do not have to bother with message extraction and "
#| "translation. However, for 3rd-party scripts developed outside of KDE, you "
#| "have to extract and translate the messages yourself. Along with your "
#| "scripts you have to also distribute a translation catalog, that includes "
#| "all translated strings. Further, your script header then must explicitly "
#| "state the catalog to load by specifying <literal>i18n-catalog</literal>."
msgid ""
"The translation functions translate the wrapped strings through &kde;'s "
"translation system to the language used in the application. Strings in "
"scripts being developed in the official &kappname; sources are automatically "
"extracted and translatable. In other words, as a &kappname; developer you do "
"not have to bother with message extraction and translation. It should be "
"noted though, that the translation only works inside the &kde; "
"infrastructure, &ie;, new strings in 3rd-party scripts developed outside of "
"&kde; are not translated. Therefore, please consider contributing your "
"scripts to &kate; such that proper translation is possible."
msgstr ""
"As funcións de internacionalización utilizan o sistema de tradución de KDE "
"para fornecer a versión das cadeas na lingua na que se executa o aplicativo. "
"As cadeas dos scripts desenvolvidos na versión oficial de &kappname; "
"extráense de maneira automática e póñense a disposición dos tradutores. É "
"dicir, os desenvolvedores de &kappname; non teñen que preocuparse das "
